-- India Beats Australia in Deciding Game of One-Day Cricket Series
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-11-02T20:31:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-02/india-beats-australia-in-deciding-game-of-one-day-cricket-series.html
Rohit Sharma scored 209 to lead  India 
to a 57-run win over  Australia  in the deciding game of their
one-day international cricket series.  Sharma hit a world record 16 sixes yesterday in Bangalore
en route to the second-highest score in one-day history as India
won the series three games to two. Captain MS Dhoni scored 62 as
India finished 383-6 in its allotted 50 overs.  Mohammed Shami and Ravindra Jadeja then took three wickets
each as Australia was bowled out for 326. James Faulkner was top
scorer for the visitors with 116.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  